{
  "stem": "17526.5",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The question is, for whom?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Krakow had 60,000 Jews before the war and now for [INAUDIBLE] services on that holiday, there were just a handful of old people, the remnants of all this Jewry.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were many more eventful experiences in Krakow, but I will not mention them now.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "From there, we went to Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was never in Warsaw before in my life.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "By standing inside the cemetery on [INAUDIBLE] Street in [INAUDIBLE] in front of the monuments of [INAUDIBLE] and [INAUDIBLE], [INAUDIBLE], all these pillars and greats of pre-war Polish Jewry, again, I could not control myself.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I felt my knees buckling again as I was moaning and sobbing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Suddenly, I felt that I was standing in a mass grave of all Jews in Europe, of Europe, at the graves of all the rabbis, scholars, thinkers, philosophers, poets, artists, merchants, physicians, scientists, the most vibrant, creative people, the crown of world Jewry going back centuries buried right here, and with them part of me also buried.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was so hard to part with this place and just walk away.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I did walk away so brokenhearted, with such a deep world-- void in my heart I wanted to scream.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "From there we went to Israel.' And I will just finish off with this here.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I will finish right here with this because this is irrelevant.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "This is not relevant to what we are talking about.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There's a few impressions of-- about leaving Poland, but this is it.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
